  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Bangladesh Floods 2015</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Heavy seasonal monsoon rains continue to affect parts of Asia resulting in flooding and landslides in several countries. The monsoon depression over the northeast Bay of Bengal intensified into Tropical Cyclone Komen which made landfall in Bangladesh on 31 July causing wind and rain that further exacerbated the situations in Bangladesh Myanmar and India. Since 24 June torrential rains in Bangladesh have caused flash floods and landslides in the low-lying areas in the south-eastern districts of Cox s Bazar Bandarban and Chittagong.</narrative>
  </description>
